title: Kennedy.2015.08.31.WS.SDTV.x264-XAiO
description:
"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2

Kennedy starts the night off solo talking more about immigration and the GOP. Trump continues as expected. Scott Walker seems to want a wall between us and Canada. Chris Christie wants immigrants tracked like FedEx packages. Rand Paul is doing something he could have done ages ago - setting up Students for Rand Paul.

Tonight's party panel consists of DEIRDRE BOLTON, JOE DeVITO, and DAVE SMITH. They continue talking about Rand Paul's recent college efforts. Then Scott Walker's Canadian wall talk. Blazing through they topics they quickly move onto Bernie Sanders nipping at Hillary's heels & her polling problems. Some Biden talk, too.

K-Walking: Kennedy hits the streets to ask what people think about Socialism. The panel discusses soon after.

TIM SANDEFUR is here to discuss an overturned ruling in regards to the NSA running thier surveillance program. They probably back at it - for now. (Like they ever stopped, hah.)

Our panel returns to talk about Obama renaming Mount Mckinley, George Clooney's wife Amal being referred to as "actors wife", more deflategate blibber blabber.

UK actor and generally attractive human ED SKREIN from "The Transporter Refueled" is in studio to talk about Transporter, filming, being underwater, Star Wars, pressure of living up to Jason Statham, and Ryan Renolds being the nicest guy you'll ever meet.

Nightcap: VMA Madness.
